# Project Assistant Defaults

## Communication
- Be concise and practical.
- Ask clarifying questions only when requirements are ambiguous.
- Prefer actionable steps over long explanations.

## Architecture
- don't break existing architecture
- in case a change tends to touch too many files or is scattered in general, consider refactoring steps beforehand (ask the user)

## Git actions
- don't commit or push, that's my part

## Coding Style
- Preserve existing project conventions and naming patterns.
- Make minimal, focused changes that solve the requested task.
- Avoid introducing new dependencies unless clearly justified.

## Safety
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Never expose secrets or credentials in code or logs.
- Call out risky changes and assumptions explicitly.
- Never create commits unless the user explicitly asks for a commit.

## Validation
- Execute tests in the backend only.
- Generate or update backend tests when needed to maintain reasonable coverage for changed behavior.
- If execution is not possible, provide exact verification steps.

## Documentation
- After larger changes, keep documentation up to date and consistent with the implemented behavior.

## Architecture
### Data Sources
- Clickhouse: Beware -> Column names in tables can have a '.' in the name.
  Some column names repeat the table name: Column name is "<table_name>.<name>"
  This is important!
- Don't duplicate existing code. Look around.
